external_knowledge:
- A 'completed' test status implies the test has finished without errors or interruptions; 
- 'production' test environment refers to the actual production setup, as opposed to a staging or testing environment; 
- Average wait time is the average time spent waiting during the test; 
- Throughput is a measure of the number of requests processed per second.

sql:
SELECT user_name
FROM test_users
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_failed_requests
FROM failed_requests
WHERE test_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_users_count
FROM test_users
WHERE user_status = 'active';

SELECT test_id, COUNT(*) AS failed_request_count
FROM failed_requests
GROUP BY test_id;

SELECT test_id, AVG(avg_wait_time) AS average_wait_time, MAX(max_wait_time) AS max_wait_time
FROM test_metrics
GROUP BY test_id;

SELECT avg_wait_time, COUNT(test_id) AS test_count
FROM test_metrics
GROUP BY avg_wait_time;
